      "message": "I think we used to use this preferVRAMUseOverFlushes() cap to force more frequent flushes on ANGLE in many places. Now it\u0027s just used in writePixels, which seems odd. I preserved it, but I\u0027d like to try removing it afterwards.\n\nThe code this was copied from used to flush with a span of the surface being written to in the else case, but that\u0027s not necessary now that this is a task in the DAG. It was used to avoid data hazards before directly whacking the pixels with GrGpu outside of the DAG.",
